IAM consists of
  Users
  Groups - A way to group our users and apply policies to them collectively
  Roles
  Policy Documents
  IAM is universal, does not apply to regions
  The root account is created on first AWS account setup, has complete admin access
  New users have no permissions when first created
  New users assigned Access Key ID & Secret Access Keys when first created, used to access AWS via APIs and CLI
  Only get to view them once, so save to secure location
Always set MFA on root account
Can create your own password rotation policies
